 1. the person who's birthday is in june is between the person traveling to prague and the person who's birthday is in may##2
 2. the person traveling to liverpool is somewhere to the right of the person who's birthday is in february##5
 3. the person who's birthday is in february is not the person traveling to san-francisco##6
 4. the person who's birthday is in november is somewhere to the right of the person who's birthday is in march##5
 5. the person who's birthday is in november is between the person who's birthday is in march and the person traveling to new-york##2
 6. the person who's birthday is in may is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to san-francisco##5
 7. the person traveling to nizza is on the far right##1
 8. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april##3
 9. the person traveling to prague is somewhere between the person who's birthday is in january and the person who's birthday is in june##7
10. the person who's birthday is in february is on the left or right of the person traveling to liverpool##3
11. the person traveling to new-york is in an even position##4
12. the person traveling to new-york is not the person who's birthday is in november##6
13. the person traveling to berlin is somewhere between the person traveling to liverpool and the person traveling to new-york##7
14. the person who's birthday is in april is on the left or right of the person traveling to new-york##3
15. the person traveling to prague is on the left or right of the person traveling to new-york##3
16. the person traveling to new-york is not the person who's birthday is in march##6
17. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in may##3
18. the person traveling to liverpool is on the right of the person traveling to london##1
19. the person who's birthday is in november is somewhere to the left of the person who's birthday is in january##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |     2      |     3     |    4    |       5       |     6     |      7      |
